definition: A miracidium stage in the Schistosoma haematobium lifecycle that occurs in the intermediate snail host.

LABEL: cercaria stage
SubClass Of: 'only in taxon' some 'parasite organism'|parasite lifecycle stage
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage that is a free-living larval stage of Digenea, developed within the germinal cells of the sporocyst or redia. A cercaria has a tapering head with large penetration glands. It may or may not have a long swimming "tail", depending on the species. The motile cercaria finds and settles in a host where it will become either an adult, or a mesocercaria, or a metacercaria, according to species.

LABEL: Schistosoma japonicum worm stage
Equivalent Class: 'parasitic worm stage' and ('only in taxon' some 'Schistosoma japonicum')

LABEL: Schistosoma japonicum egg stage
Equivalent Class: 'egg stage' and ('only in taxon' some 'Schistosoma japonicum')
definition: An egg stage in the lifecycle of Schistosoma japonicum that occurs in the mammalian host.

LABEL: oocyst stage
SubClass Of: 'only in taxon' some 'parasite organism'|parasite lifecycle stage
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage of sporozoa consisting of a zygote enclosed by cyst wall.
definition source: Mosby's Medical Dictionary, 8th edition. ï¿½ 2009, Elsevier. (http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/oocyst)

LABEL: Schistosoma haematobium 3 hour schistosomulum stage

Equivalent Class: '3 hour schistosomulum stage' and ('only in taxon' some 'Schistosoma haematobium')

LABEL: Plasmodium falciparum macrogamete stage

LABEL: procyclic trypomastigote stage
SubClass Of: 'has part' some 'cell division'|'occurs in' some ('Phlebotominae midgut' or 'Glossina midgut')|trypomastigote stage
definition: A trypomastigote stage where trypomastigote form of parasites are in dividing form. This stage occurs in fly vector.

LABEL: Schistosoma japonicum schistosomulum
SubClass Of: 'participates in' only 'Schistosoma japonicum schistosomulum stage'|Schistosoma japonicum
definition: A Schistosoma japonicum in a migratory larval form that is found within blood vessels of the definitive host and develops into the worm.

LABEL: erythrocytic schizont stage
SubClass Of: schizont stage
definition: A schizont stage that occurs in erythrocytes where trophozoites mature into a schizont and schizont produces daughter trophozoites or merozoites.
term editor: Chris Stoeckert|Jie Zheng|Matt Berriman and Priti Parikh

LABEL: Schistosoma haematobium cercaria
SubClass Of: 'participates in' only 'Schistosoma haematobium cercaria stage'|Schistosoma haematobium
definition: A Schistosoma haematobium is the parasitic larval form of the Schistosoma haematobium that develops in a freshwater snail and is released into the water.

LABEL: parasite lifecycle in host liver stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some liver|'only in taxon' some 'parasite organism'|parasite lifecycle stage
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage that occurs in the liver of the host organism. For Plasmodium species these stages can include sporozoites, trophozoites, schizonts, and merozoites.

LABEL: Trypanosoma brucei procyclic trypomastigote stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Glossina midgut'
Equivalent Class: 'procyclic promastigote stage' and ('only in taxon' some 'Trypanosoma brucei')
definition: A procyclic promastigote stage in the Trypanosoma brucei lifecycle.

LABEL: parasitic worm stage
SubClass Of: 'only in taxon' some 'parasite organism'|parasite lifecycle stage
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage of some parasites in which the parasite develops into a worm form, and undergoes maturation.

LABEL: Bulinus hepatopancreas
Equivalent Class: hepatopancreas and ('part of' some Bulinus)
definition: Hepatopancreas that is a part of or originated from a Bulinus snail.

LABEL: schizont stage
SubClass Of: 'only in taxon' some 'parasite organism'|parasite lifecycle stage
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage that is the multinucleate stage in the development of some members of the Sarcodina and some sporozoans during schizogony.

LABEL: macrogamete stage
SubClass Of: 'only in taxon' some 'parasite organism'|gamete stage
definition: A gamete stage in parasites when macrogametocytes produce macrogametes through the process known as gametogenesis.

LABEL: daughter sporocyst stage
SubClass Of: sporocyst stage

LABEL: asexual lifecycle in host red blood cell stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some erythrocyte|'only in taxon' some 'parasite organism'|parasite lifecycle stage
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage that occurs as a result of asexual replication in the red blood cells of the host organism. For Plasmodium species these stages can include merozoites, trophozoites, and schizonts.

LABEL: Plasmodium gamete
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'gamete stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is found in the midgut of a mosquito vector during gamete lifecycle stage. There are two forms of gametes: micro- and macrogametocytes.

LABEL: Plasmodium macrogamete
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'macrogamete stage')
definition: A Plasmodium gamete that is in a matured form of the macrogametocyte and found in the midgut of a mosquito vector. The macrogamete is fertilized by the microgamete, forming the zygote.

LABEL: Plasmodium microgamete
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'microgamete stage')
definition: A Plasmodium gamete that is in a matured form of exflagellated microgametocyte and found in the midgut of a mosquito vector. The microgamete fertilises the macrogamete, forming the zygote.

LABEL: Plasmodium gametocyte
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'gametocyte stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is located either in the bloodstream of the vertebrate host or midgut of mosquito vector during gametocyte stage. Gametocytes are the precursor cells of the macro- or microgametes

LABEL: Plasmodium macrogametocyte
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles midgut'|'located in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'macrogametocyte stage')
definition: A Plasmodium gametocyte that is a female gametocyte of Plasmodium and found either in the bloodstream of the vertebrate host or midgut of mosquito vector. The macrogametocyte is a precursor of the macrogamete.

LABEL: Plasmodium microgametocyte
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles midgut'|'located in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'microgametocyte stage')
definition: A Plasmodium gametocyte that is a male gametocyte of Plasmodium and found either in the bloodstream of a vertebrate host or midgut of a mosquito vector. The microgametocyte is a precursor cell of the microgamete

LABEL: Plasmodium merozoite
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'merozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is during merozoite lifecycle stage, occurs in the bloodstream of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic merozoite
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'erythrocytic merozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium merozoite that is produced in an erythrocytic schizont and released into the bloodstream of a vertebrate host. These forms invade erythrocytes.

LABEL: Plasmodium hepatic merozoite
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'hepatic merozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium merozoite that is produced in a hepatic schizont and released into the bloodstream of a vertebrate host. These forms invade erythrocytes.

LABEL: Plasmodium oocyst
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'oocyst stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is formed after traversal of the midgut wall by the ookinete stage, on the hemocoel side of the midgut wall of the mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium ookinete
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'ookinete stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is a 'banana-shaped' form originates from the round zygote. The ookinete is found in the midgut of a mosquito vector and traverses the midgut wall of a mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium schizont
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'schizont stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is a form divides through schizogony. Depending on its location, it is either called hepatic or erythrocytic schizont. The schizont is a dividing stage with 2 or more nuclei.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic schizont
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'erythrocytic schizont stage')
definition: A Plasmodium schizont that is found in infected erythrocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium hepatic schizont
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'hepatic schizont stage')
definition: A Plasmodium schizont that is found in infected hepatocytes (i.e. liver cells) of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium sporozoite
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles salivary gland'|'located in' some 'Vertebrate blood'|'located in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'sporozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is formed in the oocyst and migrates to and reside in the salivary glands of the mosquito vector. A distinction is made between oocyst-derived and salivary gland-derived sporozoites. Sporozoites invade hepatocytes in the vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium oocyst-derived sporozoite
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'oocyst-derived sporozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium sporozoite that is found in the infected hepatocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium salivary gland-derived sporozoite
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'salivary gland-derived sporozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium sporozoite that is found in the salivary glands of the mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium trophozoite
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'|'located in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'trophozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is a feeding form which has a single nucleus during the trophozoite stage. Depending on its location, it is either called hepatic or erythrocytic trophozoite.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic trophozoite
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'erythrocytic trophozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium trophozoite that is found in erythrocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic ring trophozoite
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'erythrocytic ring trophozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium erythrocytic trophozoite that has a typical 'ring-like' appearance. Ring-form trophozoites of Plasmodium are often thin and delicate, measuring on average 1/5 the diameter of the red blood cell.

LABEL: Plasmodium hepatic trophozoite
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'hepatic trophozoite stage')
definition: A Plasmodium trophozoite that is found in hepatocytes.

LABEL: Plasmodium zygote
SubClass Of: 'located in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: Plasmodium and ('participates in' only 'zygote stage')
definition: A Plasmodium that is formed after fertilization of the macrogamete by a microgamete in the midgut of the mosquito vector. This round form is the only diploid stage in the Plasmodium life cycle.

LABEL: Plasmodium gamete stage
Equivalent Class: 'gamete stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A gamete stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the midgut of a mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium macrogamete stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: 'macrogamete stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A macrogamete stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the midgut of a mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium microgamete stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: 'microgamete stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A microgamete stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the midgut of a mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium gametocyte stage
Equivalent Class: 'gametocyte stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A gametocyte stage in the lifecycle of Plasmodium.

LABEL: Plasmodium macrogametocyte stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles midgut'|'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'macrogametocyte stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A macrogametocyte stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs either in the bloodstream of a vertebrate host or the midgut of a mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium microgametocyte stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles midgut'|'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'microgametocyte stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A microgametocyte stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs either in the bloodstream of a vertebrate host or the midgut of a mosquito vector.

LABEL: Plasmodium merozoite stage
Equivalent Class: 'merozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A merozoite stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the bloodstream or hepatocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic merozoite stage
Equivalent Class: 'erythrocytic merozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: An erythrocytic merozoite stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the bloodstream of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium hepatic merozoite stage
Equivalent Class: 'hepatic merozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A hepatic merozoite stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the hepatocyte of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium oocyst stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: 'oocyst stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: An oocyst stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs on the hemocoel side of the midgut of a mosquito vector. During this stage Plasmodium ookinete invades and escapes midgut wall of mosquito and embed itself onto the exterior of the gut membrane and develop encysted zygote, called oocyst.

LABEL: Plasmodium ookinete stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: 'ookinete stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: An ookinete stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the midgut of a mosquito vector and on the outside of the midgut.

LABEL: Plasmodium schizont stage
Equivalent Class: 'schizont stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A schizont stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in erythrocytes or in hepatocytes.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic schizont stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'erythrocytic schizont stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: An erythrocytic schizont stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the infected erythrocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium hepatic schizont stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'hepatic schizont stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A hepatic schizont stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the infected hepatocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium sporozoite stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles salivary gland'|'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate blood'|'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'sporozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A sporozoite stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the salivary glands of the mosquito and invades hepatocytes in the vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium oocyst-derived sporozoite stage
Equivalent Class: 'oocyst-derived sporozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A sporozoite stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that develops in oocysts of the mosquito midgut.

LABEL: Plasmodium salivary gland-derived sporozoite stage
Equivalent Class: 'salivary gland-derived sporozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A salivary gland-derived sporozoite stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the salivary glands of the mosquito and invades hepatocytes in the vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium trophozoite stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'|'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'trophozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A trophozoite stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic trophozoite stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate erythrocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'erythrocytic trophozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: An erythrocytic trophozoite stage in the Plasmodium life cycle that occurs in erythrocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium erythrocytic ring trophozoite stage
Equivalent Class: 'erythrocytic ring trophozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: An erythrocytic ring trophozoite stage in the Plasmodium life cycle that occurs in erythrocytes of a vertebrate host. During this stage some Plasmodium merozoites undergo asexual reproduction cycle in erythrocytes and form young trophozoites that are referred to as "ring form" due to their morphology.

LABEL: Plasmodium hepatic trophozoite stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Vertebrate hepatocyte'
Equivalent Class: 'hepatic trophozoite stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A hepatic trophozoite stage in the Plasmodium life cycle that occurs in hepatocytes of a vertebrate host.

LABEL: Plasmodium zygote stage
SubClass Of: 'occurs in' some 'Anopheles midgut'
Equivalent Class: 'zygote stage' and ('only in taxon' some Plasmodium)
definition: A zygote stage in the Plasmodium lifecycle that occurs in the midgut of the mosquito vector where a microgamete and a macrogamete fertilizes each other to produce a diploid cell.

LABEL: Schistosoma haematobium adult worm stage
Equivalent Class: 'adult parasitic worm stage' and ('only in taxon' some 'Schistosoma haematobium')
definition: An adult worm stage in the Schistosoma haematobium lifecycle.

LABEL: Schistosoma japonicum adult worm stage
Equivalent Class: 'adult parasitic worm stage' and ('only in taxon' some 'Schistosoma japonicum')
definition: An adult worm stage in the Schistosoma japonicum lifecycle.

LABEL: Vertebrate blood
Equivalent Class: blood and ('part of' some 'Vertebrata <vertebrates>')
definition: Blood that is part of or originated from a vertebrate.

LABEL: Vertebrate erythrocyte
Equivalent Class: erythrocyte and ('part of' some 'Vertebrata <vertebrates>')
definition: An erythrocyte that is a part of or originated from a vertebrate.

LABEL: Vertebrate hepatocyte
SubClass Of: hepatocyte
Equivalent Class: hepatocyte and ('part of' some 'Vertebrata <vertebrates>')
definition: A hepatocyte that is a part of or originated from a vertebrate.

LABEL: Mammalia cerebrospinal fluid
Equivalent Class: 'cerebrospinal fluid' and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: Cerebrospinal fluid that is a part of or originated from a mammal.

LABEL: Mammalia skin
Equivalent Class: 'skin of body' and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: A skin that is a part of or originated from a mammalian body.

LABEL: Mammalia liver
Equivalent Class: liver and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: A liver that is a part of or originated from a mammal (Mammalia).

LABEL: Mammalia lung
Equivalent Class: lung and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: A lung that is a part of or originated from a mammal (Mammalia).

LABEL: Mammalia mesenteric vein
Equivalent Class: 'mesenteric vein' and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: A mesenteric vein that is a part of or originated from a mammal (Mammalia).

LABEL: Mammalia intestine
Equivalent Class: intestine and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: An intestine that is a part of or originated from a mammal (Mammalia).

LABEL: Schistosoma mansoni adult worm stage
Equivalent Class: 'adult parasitic worm stage' and ('only in taxon' some 'Schistosoma mansoni')
definition: An adult worm stage in the Schistosoma mansoni lifecycle.

LABEL: Mammalia blood
Equivalent Class: blood and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: Blood that is part of or originated from a mammalia.

LABEL: Mammalia macrophage
Equivalent Class: macrophage and ('part of' some Mammalia)
definition: A macrophage that is a part of or originated from a mammalia.

LABEL: Trypanosomatida metacyclic stage
SubClass Of: parasite lifecycle stage
Equivalent Class: (realizes some 'infectious agent role') and ('only in taxon' some Trypanosomatidae)
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage of trypanosomatidae in which the organism is infectious and does not multiply.

LABEL: Trypanosomatida procyclic stage
SubClass Of: parasite lifecycle stage
Equivalent Class: ('has part' some 'cell division') and ('occurs in' some ('Phlebotominae midgut' or 'Glossina midgut')) and ('only in taxon' some Trypanosomatidae)
definition: A parasite lifecycle stage of trypanosomatidae in which the organism is in dividing form and it occurs in fly vector.
